ton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2525953\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 06, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bbb1665702981995.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bbb1665702981995.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bbb1665702981995.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bbb1665702981995\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n       Secondary Process Color and Video Mnemonics\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The secondary process mnemonics instruct Uniface to perform the video feature in a secondary print or display process, that is, by printing the line a second time.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bbb1665702981995__section_zwy_w2n_hcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d569647e51\">Arguments</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"bbb1665702981995__table_d5594e1_d5595e1_d5596e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Mnemonics for Secondary Processes</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bbb1665702981995__table_d5594e1_d5595e1_d5596e1__entry__1\">Mnemonic </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bbb1665702981995__table_d5594e1_d5595e1_d5596e1__entry__2\">Explanation </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bbb1665702981995__table_d5594e1_d5595e1_d5596e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">_color</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bbb1665702981995__table_d5594e1_d5595e1_d5596e1__entry__2\">Colors for secondary process. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bbb1665702981995__table_d5594e1_d5595e1_d5596e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">_color_n</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bbb1665702981995__table_d5594e1_d5595e1_d5596e1__entry__2\">Color combination for index color\n                <var class=\"keyword varname\">n</var>, where <var class=\"keyword varname\">n</var> is an identifer from 0 through 63.\n              </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bbb1665702981995__table_d5594e1_d5595e1_d5596e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">_underscore</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bbb1665702981995__table_d5594e1_d5595e1_d5596e1__entry__2\">Video for secondary process. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bbb1665702981995__table_d5594e1_d5595e1_d5596e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">_inverse</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bbb1665702981995__table_d5594e1_d5595e1_d5596e1__entry__2\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bbb1665702981995__table_d5594e1_d5595e1_d5596e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">_high</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bbb1665702981995__table_d5594e1_d5595e1_d5596e1__entry__2\"></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bbb1665702981995__table_d5594e1_d5595e1_d5596e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">_blink</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bbb1665702981995__table_d5594e1_d5595e1_d5596e1__entry__2\"></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bbb1665702981995__section_fnl_gpn_hcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d569647e173\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bbb1665702981995__p_d63917e1_d63918e1_d63919e1\">The character used for <code class=\"ph codeph\">_underscore</code> and\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">_inverse</code> is defined in the character set section of the device\n        translation table. Use these functions for a printer that does not support video attributes\n        directly or for a display that can only perform the functions in graphics mode.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bbb1665702981995__p_d63920e1_d63921e1_d63922e1\">If you define any of the color mnemonics (that is,\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">color, color_</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">n</var>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">_color</code>, or <code class=\"ph codeph\">_color_</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">n</var>), any definition for <code class=\"ph codeph\">_inverse</code> is ignored. This also\n        means that <code class=\"ph codeph\">printer_inverse</code> in the character set section is ignored.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gox1665702984604.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface Index Color Mnemonics</a><p>Color mnemonics in the table define the 64 Uniface index color combinations.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mnu1665702982711.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Video Mode Mnemonics</a><p>Video mode mnemonics define how the device displays characters in the various video modes and combinations.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/huu1665702982941.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Secondary Process Character Mnemonics</a><p>These mnemonics define the character used in a secondary process, for example, for printers which must print a line twice to produce an underline. This technique is also used with some display devices.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525953\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525953\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Secondary Process Color and Video Mnemonics Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 06, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Secondary Process Color and Video Mnemonics The secondary process mnemonics instruct Uniface to perform the video feature in a secondary print or display process, that is, by printing the line a second time. Arguments Table 1. Mnemonics for Secondary Processes Mnemonic Explanation _color Colors for secondary process. _color_n Color combination for index color n , where n is an identifer from 0 through 63. _underscore Video for secondary process. _inverse _high _blink Description The character used for _underscore and _inverse is defined in the character set section of the device translation table. Use these functions for a printer that does not support video attributes directly or for a display that can only perform the functions in graphics mode. If you define any of the color mnemonics (that is, color, color_ n , _color , or _color_ n ), any definition for _inverse is ignored. This also means that printer_inverse in the character set section is ignored. Related Links Uniface Index Color Mnemonics Color mnemonics in the table define the 64 Uniface index color combinations. Video Mode Mnemonics Video mode mnemonics define how the device displays characters in the various video modes and combinations. Secondary Process Character Mnemonics These mnemonics define the character used in a secondary process, for example, for printers which must print a line twice to produce an underline. This technique is also used with some display devices. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}